              Is that it?</h2>
            <p style="font-family: monospace;">
            Yes - if you are happy with the default look and functionality of the forum, you can simply go ahead and invite your friends to join you there. </p>
            <p>The real power of Klavado though is that you can customise the heck out of it.</p>
            <p>What you will see on your default micro-forum is an <a href="http://www.ember-cli.com/">ember-cli</a> app and the full source code for it is available here: <a href="https://github.com/etewiah/discette-template">https://github.com/etewiah/discette-template</a> 
            </p>
            <p>To customise your micro-forum, you need to fork that repository on github and make your changes there.  You will need to have some basic web development skills to be able to do this but it really isn't too hard ;)  More detailed instructions can be found on the github site.</p>
            <p>If you have any feedback, please let me know by starting a conversation here: <a href="http://feedback.klavado.com">here</a></p>
